sp.p:
There I'm dished and done up brown;
would you believe it? she calls me a long, scraggy, outlandish
animal, and that I look like two deal boards glued together!

That's an uncommon clever girl; but, Alice,
I'm determined to turn over a new leaf with Dame Van Winkle;
the next time I see her, I'll pluck up [my] courage and say to her—

Dere is [a]der in K. drinks, dere is [a] drinks; I have [conquered]gonguered in K.
temptation at last. Bravo resolution! bravo resolution;
resolution, you shall have one glass for dat.In K., variation only in dialect form.  [Goes to table.

This is too much for human nature to support;
[this declaration is a banquet that gods might prize.Not in K.]
Beauteous angel! hear me, whilst I proclaim—

'Tis your legs are too long [by half!]Not in K.; stoop down;
[say as little as possible, and you'll not be discovered.]Not in K.
                                [He again sits.

Mr. Knickerbocker, if you please, my dear;
damme! I'm so happy I could fly to the moon, jump over a
steeple, dance a new fandango on stilts. [Dances.] Fal, lal, la.
